  Once a joint has been created, it can often be necessary to know its properties in order to change them at specific times in your game. The following functions (with their corresponding internal constants) are available to test and change joint values:
  <ul>
   <li>
    <a href="physics_joint_enable_motor.htm">
     physics_joint_enable_motor
    </a>
   </li>
   <li>
    <a href="physics_joint_get_value.htm">
     physics_joint_get_value
    </a>
   </li>
   <li>
    <a href="physics_joint_set_value.htm">
     physics_joint_set_value
    </a>
   </li>
  </ul>
  Additionally, you can use a number of constants from within
  <span>
   GameMaker
  </span>
  functions to get (or set) different properties of certain joints. These constants can all be found in the following section:
  <ul>
   <li>
    <a href="Physics_Joint_Constants.htm">
     Physics Joint Constants
    </a>
   </li>
  </ul>
